snippet.textDisplay:
Fury was a cherry pick last time gone wrong. Was away from boxing for 3 years, ballooned to 450lb, and still won the fight. He wasn't his normal sharp self ,and less power too (although he's not a power puncher). I think this time around FURY will show that there is levels to this game, and break him down with a stoppage in the 8th or 9th. Obviously Wilder is a puncher and dangerous, but if you were gonna put your mortgage on one of the two, you'd most probably put your trust in Fury.
Wilder will not be finished though, but he will have to somewhat rebuild, and it's not easy with several really good current HWs and few up an coming beasts, too. He's like 34 or 35 now too, and unless he hurries up and takes the big challenges he wouldn't have really achieved much in boxing. He hasn't got a big name win on his resume in 43 fights.
